Snyk :  
 

is a security tool. That helps to automatically find and fix the vulnerabilities . 
 
[] Step 1: Install the Snyk Security Plugin   

[] Step 2: Configure Snyk Installation (Global Tool Configuration)   

Go to Manage Jenkins > Global Tool Configuration. 

Scroll down to the "Snyk Installations" section and click Add Snyk Installation. 

Provide a Name (e.g., "Snyk Latest") for the installation. Remember this name as you will use it in your pipeline script. 

Check Install automatically and select the latest version from the dropdown menu. This ensures the Snyk CLI binaries are kept up-to-date. 

Save the changes. 

[] Step 3 Configure Snyk API Token Credential  

Obtain your API token from your Snyk account settings on the Snyk website. 

Navigate to Manage Jenkins > Manage Credentials > System > Global credentials (unrestricted) > Add Credentials. 

Select Snyk API Token as the Kind. 

Paste your Snyk API token into the Token field, provide a unique ID (e.g., my-snyk-token), and optionally add a description. 

Create the credential 

 

